observations.recommendation:
Municipal Engineer, MPDC and the BAC schedule the procurement activities as early as the first or second quarter of the year or consider adopting the Early Procurement Activities in accordance with Appendix 31 of the RIRR of RA 9184, to facilitate the implementation of planned development projects within the expected year of completion;

Human Resource Management Officer intensify the hiring of qualified personnel for MPDC and MEO to ensure effective project monitoring and enable timely recommendations for changes in plans and programs, without compromising the target completion date; and

Concerned Department Heads stop the practice of appropriating funds in lump-sum or generic terms and ensure that projects are described with sufficient details in order not to cause more delays in implementing the project, in accordance with Article 454 (d) of the IRR of R.A. 7160 and Budget Operations Manual for LGUs.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor, through the Municipal Administrator, agreed to issue an updated Executive Order for the reconstitution of the Inventory Committee’s members, duties, and responsibilities, and designate a focal person from each office to monitor and account for supplies and properties, for consolidation by the GSO.
Further, to address the other issues, we reiterated our prior year’s audit recommendation which the Management through the concerned officer/committee agreed to implement, as follows:
The GSO prepare PCs for every class of PPE and SCs per stock number as a source document in conducting reconciliation with the records of the Accounting Office;
The Municipal Accountant prepare ledger cards for PPE and Supplies to document all the necessary details of PPE and inventories and to be used as source documents in conducting reconciliation with the records of the GSO;
The GSO and Inventory Committee complete the physical count of properties and supplies and submit the RPCPPE on or before January 31 of each year and the RPCI not later than July 31 and January 31 each year; and
The Inventory Committee conduct the one-time cleansing of PPE following the guidelines and procedures in COA Circular 2020-006.

a. The Local Treasurer and the Local Accountant to submit to the LSB of the certified statement containing the following enumerated below, not later than July 15 of the current year as basis for the formulation of SEF budget.
I. Actual SEF income for the immediately preceding fiscal year;
II. Actual SEF income for the first two quarters of the current year;
III. The estimated SEF income for the last two quarters of the current year; and
IV. The annual estimates for the ensuing year.
b. The LSB shall furnish the Local Budget Officer, the Local Accountant, and the Local Treasurer a copy of the SEF Budget as basis for disbursement or certification of availability of funds and for recording purposes.

