We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Accounting Office to coordinate with the Municipal School Board (MSB) and communicate with DepEd Tuburan District Office and request for the immediate liquidation of outstanding cash advances grated to DepEd officials and employees;

Require the MSB to authorize the municipal treasurer to disburse funds from the SEF pursuant to the budget prepared and in accordance with existing rules and regulations;

Recommended for write off all unsettled cash advances which had been in the books for over ten (10) years in accordance with the guidelines set forth under COA Circular 2016-005 on the Guidelines and Procedures on the Write-off of Dormant Receivable Accounts, Unliquidated Cash Advances and Fund Transfers of National Government Agencies (NGAs), Local Government Agencies (LGUs) and Government-Owned and Controlled Corporations (GOCCs).

Recommendation:
