We have recommended and management agreed to:

1.	Prioritize projects only after the technical viability of the projects has been ascertained through preliminary engineering study;

2.	Evaluate the need of the projects that remained unimplemented as of year-end and recommend to the Municipal Development Council the revision of projects that are not feasible under the 20% Development Fund;

3.	Direct the different implementing offices to execute all PPAs planned for implementation during the year and submit accomplishment reports on a monthly or quarterly basis to the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator (MPDC); and

4.	Advise the MPDC to monitor and evaluate the implementation of the PPAs, and submit periodic reports to the Municipal Mayor incorporating issues and concerns affecting the execution of projects.

We reiterate our recommendation that the General Services Officer Designate do the following courses of action:

To prepare a complete physical inventory report of PPE using the prescribed form with complete description, whereabouts and condition of the properties under the remarks portion;

To reconcile the results of the physical count with the Schedule of PPE maintained by the Accounting Unit and the Accountant to provide allowance for depreciation on movable PPEs.

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare immediately the certified list of taxpayers showing the names and amounts due and collectible for the taxpayers;

Instruct the Municipal Assessor to submit immediately, and regularly provide the Municipal Treasurer’s Office with the Real Property Assessment Roll so that the MTO can update its records;

Coordinate with other offices and install an effective collection scheme to increase tax collection.
